    "comment": "Rationale: By ultrastructure studies, authors find that the absence of p75NTR results in a significant reduction in the number of synaptic vesicles and active zones, as well as in the density of the readily releasable pool (RRP) of vesicles.\n20/01/2021 Dnyanada:\nThe paper shows that p75NTR KO leads to a reduction in the number of SV/AZ/RRPs, however, simply based on ultrastructural data, it is difficult to attribute the consequence of this on synaptic BP. Hence, a generic term \"presynaptic modulation of chemical synaptic transmission\" was chosen.. Experimental description: The C57BL/6 J strain B6.129S4-Ngfrtm1Jae/J p75NTR-/- mice and their control pairs were purchased from The Jackson Laboratory (Sacramento, California, USA).",
